==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Intwine
<hw>In*twine"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Entwine</er>.]</ety> <def>To twine or twist into, or together; to
wreathe; <as>as, a wreath of flowers <ex>intwined</ex></as>.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>entwine</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intwine</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Intwine
<hw>In*twine"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To be or to become
intwined.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intwinement</ent>⟦br⟧
